<div class="row section">
  <div class="col s12">
    <h2>Finding Help</h2>

    <p class='flow-text'>Support for victims and witnesses of racist and xenophobic attacks.</p>

    <p>If you or someone you know has been affected by hate crime, there are various organisations that can offer free and confidential support and advice. You can find more information, including contact details, on these websites:</p>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'Victim Support', 'https://www.victimsupport.org.uk', target: '_blank' %></h5>
      <p>Victim Support is the leading independent charity for people affected by crime in England and Wales. Their services are free, confidential and available to anyone in England and Wales, regardless of whether you have reported the crime or how long ago it happened.</p>
      <p><%= link_to 'Visit the website', 'https://www.victimsupport.org.uk', target: '_blank' %> or contact the support line on 0300 303 1927.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'The Monitoring Group', 'http://www.tmg-uk.org', target: '_blank' %></h5>

      <p>The Monitoring Group is a leading anti-racist charity that promotes civil rights and provides help to traumatised victims of racial and religious harassment.</p>
      <p>They can be reached on 020 7582 7438, or via the <%= link_to 'form on their website', 'http://www.tmg-uk.org/do-you-need-help/do-you-need-help/', target: '_blank' %>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'Citizens Advice', 'https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk', target: '_blank' %></h5>
      <p>Citizens Advice provide free, confidential and independent advice from over 3,500 locations across the UK. These include high streets, community centres, doctors' surgeries, courts and prisons.</p>
      <p>Advice can be given in person, by phone, or by email. You can find contact details and your nearest citizens advice office <%= link_to 'on their website', 'https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk', target: '_blank' %>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'True Vision', 'http://www.report-it.org.uk/home', target: '_blank' %></h5>

      <p>True Vision is a website designed to provide you with information about Hate Crime. It includes an <%= link_to 'extensive list of organisations', 'http://www.report-it.org.uk/organisations_that_can_help', target: '_blank' %> that can provide information and support</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>